& [SourceSet] is selected_theorem_neighborhood
  + [source_001] is https://www.math.lsu.edu/~pcnguyen/papers_html/Phuc_NS_regularity_08_16_14_Simplify_3D.pdf
    = role: epsilon-regularity and local pressure quantities
    = extracted_boundary: accepted criteria keep pressure quantities such as D(p) explicit alongside velocity quantities; pressure smallness is not automatically removed by local velocity control
  + [source_002] is https://sebastian-hensel.com/master_thesis.pdf
    = role: local suitable weak solutions and harmonic pressure decomposition
    = extracted_boundary: local pressure can be decomposed using harmonic pressure and local pressure terms, but this supplies a frame, not project-tail smallness
  + [source_003] is https://arxiv.org/pdf/2606.08352
    = role: harmonic pressure caution
    = extracted_boundary: modulo-harmonic formulations are needed because harmonic pressure behavior can defeat naive pressure-gradient or oscillation intuition
  + [source_004] is https://par.nsf.gov/servlets/purl/10333954
    = role: local pressure expansion for intermittent/local-energy settings
    = extracted_boundary: local pressure expansion estimates pressure parts under specified far-field controls, suggesting a possible comparison frame but not a theorem for the current source tail budget
  + [source_005] is https://www.uni-ulm.de/fileadmin/website_uni_ulm/mawi.inst.020/skipper/NotesCKN_Jack_2.pdf
    = role: CKN target language
    = extracted_boundary: local regularity criteria preserve velocity-pressure smallness as the target object

& [ProspectResult] is no_bridge_target_found
  + [result] is negative_prospect
  + [reason] is known pressure-estimate frameworks either retain pressure as an independent local quantity, require a precise pressure decomposition with controlled remainders, or assume far-field controls not supplied by the source tail formula
  + [accepted_positive_neighborhood] is local pressure estimates can bound pressure components from velocity/source terms after a decomposition is fixed
  + [missing_for_project] is threshold-small same-cylinder pressure output from the source's velocity/enstrophy/cutoff/transport/log-loss budget
  + [first_missing_feature] is no_velocity_enstrophy_cutoff_budget_to_pressure_smallness_theorem
  + [admission_status] is boundary_only

& [TheoremBoundary] is the refined obstruction
  + [not_enough_001] is Calderon-Zygmund pressure representation from u tensor u alone
    = reason: it yields pressure estimates from velocity norms but does not absorb cutoff, transport, nonlocal, and log-loss terms into epsilon smallness
  + [not_enough_002] is local suitable pressure decomposition
    = reason: it names p_h and p_0 slots but requires component-level bounds not supplied by the source tail formula
  + [not_enough_003] is local energy or epsilon regularity pressure criterion
    = reason: it requires pressure quantity smallness in the criterion rather than deriving it from the current tail budget
  + [not_enough_004] is far-field pressure expansion
    = reason: it requires explicit far-field control and scale decay, while the source formula carries bounded tail terms and an outer logarithmic loss

& [DevelopedUnderstanding] is the current shape of meaning
  + [old_shape] is perhaps velocity and enstrophy budgets can be promoted through local pressure estimates into pressure smallness
  + [new_shape] is pressure estimates provide comparison language but not the missing threshold bridge for this source route
  + [meaning_gained] is the Navier-Stokes pressure-tail lane is saturated unless a specific theorem supplies scale decay or smallness for the projection remainder from exactly these budgets
